].

To draw rigid conclusions about the wind power availability, the energy conversion process should be taken into account, which is outside of the scope of this study. Archer [
51
] argues that the 5th percentile can be used as a generic proxy for the wind power availability. Previously it was shown that allowing a variable harvesting height greatly increases the 5th percentile of both the wind speed and wind power density probability distributions and thereby greatly increase the wind power availability.
